<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="339" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5914/219½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">27 March, 1917</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I entirely approve. In
                            view of recent despatches from Denmark, would it be possible to complete
                            the transfer before the Congress meets,—I mean, of course, so far as the
                            payment of the money is concerned and the formal transfer of title? I
                            hope that this can be arranged.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>